sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant KServe as KServe Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Istio as Istio Sidecar<br/>15006/TCP mTLS
    participant API as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Runner as HPUModelRunner<br/>In-Process
    participant HPU0 as HPU Device<br/>TP Rank 0
    participant HPU1 as HPU Device<br/>TP Rank N
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>S3/PVC/HF Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over API,S3: Flow 3: Model Loading (Startup)
    API->>S3: HTTPS/443 Download model weights<br/>Auth: AWS IAM / Bearer Token
    S3-->>API: Model artifacts
    API->>Runner: Load model into memory
    Runner->>HPU0: DMA transfer via PCIe<br/>Load weights to HPU VRAM

    Note over Client,HPU1: Flow 1: Inference Request
    Client->>KServe: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    KServe->>Istio: Route to pod<br/>mTLS
    Istio->>API: HTTP/8000<br/>plaintext (within pod)
    API->>Runner: Process inference request
    Runner->>HPU0: Forward pass<br/>PCIe / Device Memory
    HPU0->>HPU1: HCCL All-Reduce<br/>Gaudi NIC (Tensor Parallel)
    HPU1-->>HPU0: Aggregated result
    HPU0-->>Runner: Output tokens
    Runner-->>API: Generated response
    API-->>Istio: HTTP/8000 Response<br/>(SSE for streaming)
    Istio-->>KServe: mTLS
    KServe-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over API,HPU1: Flow 2: Disaggregated Prefill-Decode (NIXL, Optional)

    participant Prefill as Prefill Instance<br/>HPU
    participant Decode as Decode Instance<br/>HPU

    Prefill->>Decode: NIXL/UCX KV-cache transfer<br/>GDR / TCP<br/>plaintext (cluster network)
    Note over Prefill,Decode: KV-cache from HPU VRAM/DRAM<br/>to remote instance
